summary:
The keyword defer in Swift is not often encountered. Especially when you start developing. Nevertheless it has a certain usefulness and can be very useful.
Definition # defer is a Swift keyword used to define code to execute before leaving the current scope:
func changeTitle(_ title: String) { defer { print(&#34;After&#34;) } print(&#34;Before&#34;) myTitleLabel.text = title } At first sight and if we only consider the order in which the instructions are written, we could believe that we will have the following output:
